FREQUENTLY ASKED QUESTIONS

Q1: I'm an academic researcher. Can I use Loucetios for free?
A: Yes! Use under AGPLv3. If you publish or distribute your work, cite Loucetios.

Q2: I'm building a commercial product. Do I need a commercial license?
A: If your product is closed-source or proprietary, yes. Contact ceh303@gmail.com

Q3: I'm a student building a project in a startup. What do I need?
A: If the startup will open-source the project, AGPLv3. If not, commercial license.

Q4: Can I modify Loucetios under AGPLv3?
A: Yes, but your modifications must also be open-sourced under AGPLv3.

Q5: What if I use Loucetios in a web service (SaaS)?
A: You must obtain a Commercial License. AGPLv3 requires that SaaS code be
   open-sourced, which is unacceptable for proprietary business models.

Q6: How much does a Commercial License cost?
A: Negotiable. Email ceh303@gmail.com with your use case.

Q7: Can I get a Commercial License for a research spin-out company?
A: Yes. Contact ceh303@gmail.com to discuss academic pricing.

Q8: What if I violate the license?
A: Your license is terminated, and you must cease use immediately.
   Copyright holder may pursue legal action.

